programme.title: The Bomber
programme.desc: Part 3 of this epic tale of war, love, betrayal, and sabotage. When Andrey, Katya, and Linko crash land in the field of battle, they find themselves in a struggle for survival that test the bonds of friendship.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Sofia Central Prison, Sofia, Bulgaria
programme.desc: With a crumbling foundation fit for demolition, Sofia Central prison is inhospitable for anyone, including criminals. With multiple prisoner cells, bunks stacked 3 high and horrid isolation cells, prisoners live idly behind bars for 23 hours a day.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Miami, Dade County Jail Boot Camp, Miami, Florida, USA
programme.desc: The toughest divisions of the Miami Dade: Boot Camp gives minor offenders a chance to escape the prison through unforgiving drills and rules. To many it is a better alternative to The M-D County Jail where murderers and rapists have their own rules.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A hairy, aggressive monster is said to haunt northern New Zealand. The Maori named it Moehau, in honor of the highest peak in a nearby mountain range. This half-man, half-gorilla is a true New Zealand legend, just as Bigfoot is for North Americans.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A monster has terrorized Belize for centuries. It is described as a small man, three-feet tall, with an ugly face, hands without thumbs and inverted feet. According to legend it wears a red hat, dresses in animal skins and carries a menacing machete.

programme.title: The Wheelchair President
programme.desc: At the height of war, President Franklin D. Roosevelt inspired millions with visions of a new and better post-war world. Set against the epic scale of World War II, Professor David Reynolds presents an intimate biography of a man who was burdened.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Tent City Jail, Phoenix, Arizona, USA
programme.desc: Old army tents left over from the Korean War house prisoners instead of cells. The Sheriff is a hard man who refuses to spend any more than he has to on his prisoners. Harassment and humiliation is a part of everyday life at Tent City.

programme.title: Behind Bars The Worlds Toughest Prisons: Antanimora Prison, Madagascar
programme.desc: Desperate overcrowding, rats, and disease come standard in Antanimora Prison. Surrounded by the capital Antananarivo, it's bursting at the seams. It was originally built for 800 prisoners, but now it contains more than 3,000 prisoners.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: For almost two centuries, tourists have been flocking to the waters of Lake Champlain hoping against the odds to glimpse the lake monster they’ve affectionately dubbed Champ. Learn about one of the oldest monster legends in the world.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The Mothman legend captivates tourists from all over the world, who pilgrimage to Point Pleasant, West Virginia, to visit sighting locations, question locals and tour the Mothman museum or buy Mothman memorabilia. The monster is now a local celebrity.

programme.title: Caught on Camera: Gangs in the UK
programme.desc: Thugs terrorize our towns and neighborhoods, from smack dealing, to street brawling, mugging to burglary.

programme.title: Caught on Camera: Anarchy in the UK
programme.desc: Masked protesters bring mayhem to the streets of London. Shocking footage puts a rioter behind bars, and a wasted Santa experiences the perils of too much Christmas spirit.

programme.title: Galapagos Realm of Giant Sharks
programme.desc: This film reconstructs the life of famed marine biologist and environmental pioneer Jacques Cousteau using a fascinating mix of wildlife footage, archive material and elaborate reenactments.

programme.title: The Phoenix Incident
programme.desc: This nail-biting UFO conspiracy thriller chronicles the US military’s alleged engagement with extra-terrestrial forces on the famous night of the Phoenix Lights.

programme.title: The Ninth Gate
programme.desc: A rare book dealer, while seeking out the last two copies of a demon text, gets drawn into a conspiracy with supernatural overtones. Starring: Johnny Depp, Frank Langella, Lena Olin.

programme.title: Antboy
programme.desc: 12-year-old Pelle is bitten by an ant and develops superpowers. Aided by comic book nerd Wilhelm, Pelle creates a secret identity as superhero Antboy.

programme.title: The Heist
programme.desc: A comedy centered on three museum security guards who devise a plan to steal back the artworks to which they have become attached after they are transferred to another museum. Starring: Morgan Freeman, Christopher Walken, Joseph McKenna, Wynn Everett.

programme.title: Strike One
programme.desc: A young boy living in a gang-controlled place finds that he might be able to get by in his neighborhood, but possibly never get out because he is affiliated with gang-related activities. Feat: Alan Corral, Danny Trejo & James Russo.

programme.title: Faults
programme.desc: Ansel Roth is recruited to kidnap and deprogramme Claire, a victim of the mysterious cult called Faults. Yet Claire proves to be a formidable captive.

programme.title: Moonwalkers
programme.desc: What if Apollo 11 never actually made it? What if, in reality, Stanley Kubrick secretly shot the famous images of the moon landing in a studio, working for the US administration? Feat Rupert Grint & Ron Perlman.

programme.title: Adult World
programme.desc: From the producer of Assassination Nation, this dark and racy satirical drama sees eccentric college graduate Amy (Emma Roberts: We’re the Millers) begrudgingly accept a job at a sex shop, all while she pursues a relationship with her teacher.

programme.title: SuperBob
programme.desc: When postman Robert is struck by a meteor, he is bestowed with super powers. 6 years later, Bob finally gets a day off from his superhero duties and tries to get a shot at love. Starring: Brett Goldstein, Catherine Tate, Natalia Tena.

programme.title: Moomins
programme.desc: Discover the magical world of the Moomins in the classic and universally-loved animation series. Join young Moomin, Moominpappa, Moominmamma and their friends Snufkin, Little My, Sniff and Snork Maiden in their exciting adventures in Moominvalley.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Danger Death Ray
programme.desc: Danger Death Ray: A slick secret agent investigates an evil organization that stole a top secret death ray.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Samson vs. The Vampire Women
programme.desc: While Mike and the Bots wrestle with Samson vs. the Vampire Women, TV's Frank is assumed into Second Banana Heaven.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Violent Years
programme.desc: Jam Handy shows the world the glory of sexism with electric kitchen appliances and Ed Wood analyzes the world of criminals spoiled by their parents.

programme.title: The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living and Became Mixed-Up Zombies
programme.desc: A couple of slackers stumble across a cult of monsters at a carnival.

programme.title: Home Economics Story
programme.desc: Kay wants to go to Iowa State College and major in home economics. She and her friends have a great time in school and learn about the diverse careers that a degree in Home Economics can lead to.

programme.title: Turkey Day!
programme.desc: MST3K Turkey Day!: A compilation of new introductions for the infamous Turkey Day marathon as well as a nostalgic look back on the Comedy Central fan-favorite marathon of Mystery Science Theater.

programme.title: Juvenile Delinquency?
programme.desc: A band of no-good punks beat a guy for driving too slow and steal his mechanical pencil, before arriving to pick up their missing member Jamie, the son of the man they've just beaten.

programme.title: First Date
programme.desc: What to Do on a Date. Nick wants to take Kay out on a date, but isn't sure what they'd do. The short offers ideas like taffy pulls and scavenger sales. Nothing says romantic quite like a scavenger sale.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts: Are You Ready for Marriage?
programme.desc: A high school senior named Sue and her boyfriend want to get married right after Sue graduates. A marriage counselor discourages the young couple from entering into a hasty marriage.

programme.title: A Case of Spring Fever
programme.desc: An animated pixie named Coily grants a man his wish that all springs disappear...a wish that he soon regrets.

programme.title: Last Clear Chance
programme.desc: Friendly Patrolman Hal Jackson visits the Dixon family to instruct their youngest son, Alan, in the art of safe and courteous driving.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts: Alphabet Antics
programme.desc: A charming rhyme for children that teaches them the alphabet, including many now politically-incorrect things, dangerous sequences, and some plagiarism.

programme.title: MST3K Shorts: Chicken of Tomorrow
programme.desc: We learn what is being done "today" to create the Chicken of Tomorrow (complete with the growth process of the chicken), with a side mention of how important gas stations and oil are to the poultry industry.

programme.title: Reefer Madness Riffer Edition
programme.desc: Yes, Reefer Madness let the world know that even a single dose of marijuana caused insane laughter, enhanced skill at ragtime piano, the inability to avoid hitting old men with your car, and defenestration.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Crawling Eye
programme.desc: Things start to look eerily familiar to scientists Crevett and Brooks when mountain climbers begin losing their heads in the Trollenberg Mountains.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Slime People
programme.desc: The crew puts Commando Cody on trial for crimes against reality after watching the sixth episode of Radar Men while slime monsters invade Los Angeles in The Slime People.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Moon Zero Two
programme.desc: Moon Zero Two: The crew stages their own moon landing pageant as they watch the film about an astronaut hired to capture an asteroid made of sapphires.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Untamed Youth
programme.desc: Joel invents a pipe with a smoke detector and a sprinkler system built in for the invention exchange. The guys watch a 1950s teen flick about youths sentenced to manual labor at a cotton farm.

programme.title: RiffTrax: House on Haunted Hill: Three Riffer Edition
programme.desc: Long before lunatic millionaires Michael Jackson or Rick Rockwell, there was Vincent Price's Frederic Loren, an eccentric, unhappily married fop who offers a huge cash prize to anyone who can stay overnight in the house on Haunted Hill.

programme.title: RiffTrax: The Guy From Harlem: The Guy From Harlem
programme.desc: As you'd expect from the title, The Guy from Harlem is set entirely in Miami. It's the story of private eye and titular Guy, Al Connors, a man with a reputation.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Best of RiffTrax Villains: Best of RiffTrax Villains
Missile to the Moon
programme.desc: The title says it all, a missile goes to the moon! Only there are people in the missile so it's not really a missile but should more precisely be referred to as a rocket!

programme.title: Buffalo Rider
programme.desc: Buffalo Rider: When you really stop and think about it, there are two kinds of movies: movies where rugged men punch mountain lions, and movies where this sadly does not happen.

programme.title: Fun in Balloon Land
programme.desc: We would say that Fun In Balloonland is our favourite RiffTrax movie, but there's just one problem: it's hard to really describe it as a movie. It is an event. To attempt to describe its plot to you, would be like attempting to divide by zero.

programme.title: RiffTrax: David and Hazel: A Story in Communication
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Buffalo Rider: Buffalo Rider
programme.desc: Buffalo Rider: When you really stop and think about it, there are two kinds of movies: movies where rugged men punch mountain lions, and movies where this sadly does not happen.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Abraxas: Guardian of the Universe
programme.desc: Abraxas, Guardian of the Universe, follows the heroic exploits of a galactic defender, played by Jesse Ventura, who comes to Earth to-wait, wait, that can't be right.

programme.title: Total Riff Off Episode 5: Animals Behaving Badly
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Warriors of the Wasteland
programme.desc: So the Warriors of the Wasteland drive around in their admittedly sweet cars, sporting their admittedly heinous hairstyles, kinda resenting books and occasionally massacring an outpost of survivors.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy Sumo
programme.desc: Edo, Japan's capital city during the Middle Ages. Oggy is in conflict with Lord Bob. Olivia suggests that they settle their differences with a Sumo wrestling ceremony. Olivia is keen to help her contestant win, but the cockroaches interfere….

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Marky Da Vinci
programme.desc: Venice 1500. Oggy is a failed artist, compared to Marky, who's a multi-talented genius, in both art and science. Marky invents revolutionary machines which enable Joey and DD to pilfer Oggy's spaghetti supply.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 1
programme.desc: Om Nom, the hero of the world-famous Cut the Rope game series, is a cute little candy-eating monster. One day, he mysteriously shows up at the doorstep of one boy's house, and this marked the beginning of many fun adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 2
programme.desc: Just when Om Nom thought all of the adventures are behind him and he can finally get some rest with the bowl of candies in hand, something unexpected happened ... Visit breathtaking locations and meet amazing new creatures in Om Nom Stories!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 3
programme.desc: Join Om Nom in the amazing journey around the world, where he tastes the national sweets and meets many new friends! Try to guess all the countries Om Nom visits this Season! Om Nom decided to start his own video blog!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 4
programme.desc: An astronaut, a magician, or a humble waiter? In search for his dream job, Om Nom fights zero-gravity, delivers letters and performs magic tricks.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Boredom Blues / Puppy Love
programme.desc: Agent Brains is extremely bored. She asks Fred to turn Friday into a tennis racket so she can participate in a tournament. / Brains and Fred fall in love with a puppy but Friday gets suspicious and tries to get rid of it ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Unready to Rumble / Mom Bot
programme.desc: Fred wants to impress Nora and decides to face the brutal bully Wally K. He counts on Friday to help him out. / Fred plans the biggest house party of the year and invites the whole school. His headmaster is sceptical and wants to talk to Fred's mother.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Agent Alpha One / Science Unfair
programme.desc: Brains has to go on a mission with her big idol – Agent Alpha One! But when both had to fight a giant octopus, Agent Alpha One behaves strangely ... / Fred wants to skip classes and sneaks into a science fair.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Fred's Close Shave / Girlfriends Are a Girl's Best Friend
programme.desc: Brains gets bitten by weird bugs and grows a big beard! / All the girls in school are obsessed with a series of romantic books – except for Brains! Fred explains to her that she doesn't act like a normal girl ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Red Button / Crushing Friday
programme.desc: Brains is gone for the weekend but she fears to leave Fred alone with the controls – especially the Red Button! / Fred and Friday take part in a robot battle tournament to compete against the champions.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Fake Robot Parents / Weather Boy
programme.desc: Brains' robot-parents pick her up from school, almost revealing her cover as an agent. / Fred is sick of the rainy weather and asks Friday to turn into a vacuum cleaner that sucks clouds so he can swim in Brains' pool.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: You've Got Fe-mail / Brains Math Problem
programme.desc: Fred wrote thousands of love emails to Nora but never actually sent them. By mistake, he sends all of them ... / Brains is sick of pretending to be an average student to not break her cover.

programme.title: Grossology: Fartzilla
programme.desc: Tormented for years, an evil genius builds a giant, fart-powered robot to get revenge on his sadistic older brother.

programme.title: Grossology: The Perfect Stink
programme.desc: Sloppy Joe, the world's filthiest villain, is on a quest to concoct the world's most potent stink bomb.

programme.title: Grossology: Scab's For You
programme.desc: The Scab Fairy (the Tooth Fairy's grosser cousin) is taking scabs without even leaving a quarter under kid's pillows!

programme.title: Grossology: When Ya Gotta Go
programme.desc: A crime wave has hit the city and the cops can't stop it; they're all down with a case of the runs!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Dancing Rasta On a Ice
programme.desc: In their bid to raise the Super League trophy, the world’s greatest soccer team, Supa Strikas, must adventure through the world of soccer.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Cool Joe Loses His Groove
programme.desc: Wearing the captain’s armband is a great honour for Dancing Rasta, but after a fall in the Himalayas, he is concerned about his leadership abilities.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The Lost Star
programme.desc: Funky Cool Joe gets into the rhythm before every game with his favourite song. But when the evil Toni Vern switches his record, the star player can’t understand why he’s useless on the field!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Compound Compromised
programme.desc: On a trip to Rio to play Brazilian masters-of-flair, Club Palmentieri, Supa Strikas are demolished in a “friendly” beach game. The only person who can help them is a legend of the game ... who has been missing for thirty years!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Blasts From The Past
Supa Strikas: Between Friends
programme.desc: Supa Strikas travel to Mexico to confront the biggest goalkeeper in the Super League. Shakes uncovers De Los Santos’ past, and makes an amazing discovery in the big man’s hometown: mysterious Aztec ruins ... and the origins of the game itself!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Instinct Extinct
programme.desc: Supa Strikas face Twisting Tiger’s old team, FC Nakama, but Nakama boss Ura Giri releases a DVD of all Tiger’s secret moves to punish him for leaving the team. Now the famous midfielder needs to find new moves ... and fast!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Inside Out
programme.desc: Because of the magical powers of a witch's spyglass, the roles of the household inhabitants are reversed: the cockroaches are now as big as Oggy while the cats become as small as the cockroaches! Oggy and Jack try to get the priceless object back.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy's Double
programme.desc: Oggy is sprinkling the hedges in his garden when he sees a cat, who looks exactly like him, walk past him. He is amazed and he invites the cat over for a cup of tea. The cats look at each other: they are look-alikes! Jack shows up at Oggy's house….

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Night Watchmen
programme.desc: Oggy and Jack are night watchmen in a nuclear power station. The roaches don't want to miss that! They go in the control room, and in two ticks, all the warning lights turn red! Oggy chases after them and ends up in the heart of the reactor...Oops!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: The Cicada and the Cockroach
programme.desc: During a sunny afternoon, Oggy is driving his scooter, smiling, when a flying insect smashes in his teeth. It is a cicada. Because she is hurt, Oggy picks her up and takes her home to take care of her. Soon the cicada song drives the roaches nuts.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: The Ancestor
programme.desc: Oggy is gardening peacefully when he suddenly falls into a hole and finds himself in a cave! Lost among several rock paintings, Oggy finds a big and hairy prehistoric cockroach stuck in a block of ice. It won't be long until the roaches unfreeze him!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Ugly, Dirty and Good
programme.desc: The roaches try to break into the fridge but Oggy cuts off the cable that the insects were climbing to reach their objective. Joey falls and remains lying on the floor. But when Oggy is about to punish him, Joey smiles at him tenderly.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Just Married!
programme.desc: Jack is getting married, he chooses Oggy as his best man. Even though they haven't been invited, the cockroaches are of course attending the party! Jack gives an anti-cockroaches detector to Oggy to help him get rid of those damn insects.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories
programme.desc: Super-Noms' adventures continue! In this season, you will witness some unexpected comebacks of your favourite characters that will help Noms to fight the evil.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 7
programme.desc: In this new season, our superheroes return and so do their foes! You will see some acquaintances among the villains but their moves will be far from familiar ... However, Dr. Cheddar has something special to help Om Nom and Om Nelle in their adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 8
programme.desc: Super-Noms always come to the rescue! However, in this season, rather than saving the whole city, they'll have to focus on their friends and protect them from the mischief!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 9
programme.desc: In this season, Super-Noms will discover that superpowers are not always helpful, and that kindness, bravery, and intelligence are the real gems that can solve any situation!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Basket Bunny / Bottle Racquet
programme.desc: Braianna is the star of her school basketball team but right in the middle of a game, she has to leave to take care of an intergalactic chicken ... / Fred wants to build a floating island made of bottles ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Day the Boys Stood Still / Mouse Trap
programme.desc: Fred tries to get Brains interested in his hobby – mud racing. In his attempt to convince her he awakens the demons of the mud. / Brains has to take care of Mr. Boots, a new recruit that is also a tiny mouse.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: King of the Sewer Bears / The Smelly Princess
programme.desc: Fred is named the King of the Sewer Bears due to his special birthmark. But the power is going to his head ... / Agent Brains has to protect princess Iria but her smell is so beguiling that you have to fulfil her every wish.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: The Dung Beetle / The Ride of Their Lives
programme.desc: Braianna is invited to a TV animal show but Corky is jealous and tries everything to stop her from going. / Fred and Sir Percival want to try out the new attraction in the amusement park. Friday is sad as he has to stay at home ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Return of the Dirt Demonds / The New Fred
programme.desc: Fred wants to make a monster film to impress Nora – and goes on a search for real monsters! Fred inadvertently hurts Nora with his words. He orders Friday to speak for him from now on ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Coach Dad / The Thing that Slept Over
programme.desc: Fred is not happy: His dad becomes the new gym teacher and all of Fred's classmates are exhausted! / Agent Brains investigates a slumber party to find out who has the energy-sucking leech Slimetra.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Egghead's Revenge / Surprise Day Off
programme.desc: Egghead wants to take revenge on Brains as she receives an award for being the smartest scientist. / All the teachers have been kidnapped by Potatoids – and have mutated into babies!

programme.title: Fight Stars: Ronda Rousey
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including Rowdy Ronda Rousey, and her old training partner, Kayla Harrison.

programme.title: Fight Stars: Zou Shiming
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including the biggest boxing star in China, Zou Shiming.

programme.title: Fight Stars: Nicola Adams
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring. British boxing champion Nicola Adams OBE, a 2x flyweight Olympic gold medalist and holds an undefeated record title for the WBO female flyweight title.

programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including some females dominating the fight world like Angela Lee and Paige VanZant.

programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including Wladimir Klitschko's 2017 return to the ring and Hollywood's Idris Elba entering the world of combat sports.

programme.title: Fight Stars: Tyson Fury
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including the rise and fall of Tyson Fury and Nicola Adams exciting start to 2017.

programme.title: Fight Stars: Floyd Mayweather
programme.desc: The best combat sport stars in the ring, on the canvas and living it up outside of their sport, including Floyd Mayweather Jr and his post boxing career and some anti trash talkers in the sport.

programme.title: Fight Stars: Anderson Silva

programme.title: Hunter: Under Suspicion

programme.title: Hunter: The Reporter

programme.title: Hunter: Room Service

programme.title: Hunter: Shadows of the Past

programme.title: Hunter: The Grab

programme.title: Hunter: Dead or Alive

programme.title: Deadly Women

programme.desc: Known as “black widows,” these women kill their spouses, lovers and children for profit. Murder for them becomes a business. Their trade is murder. Their profit? Blood money.

programme.title: Deadly Women

programme.title: The FBI Files: Melissa Brannen: Missing
programme.desc: In 1989, residents of a close-knit apartment community in Virginia gathered for a holiday celebration. For Tammy Brannen and five-year-old daughter Melissa, Christmas was always a special time. Then, without warning, the little girl was gone.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Unabomber
programme.desc: For nearly two decades a mathematical genius with delusions of single-handedly destroying industrial society, planted or mailed powerful bombs to unsuspecting innocent victims.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Murdering Cowboy
programme.desc: The sun set on the Wild West long ago, but some people refused to notice. Claude Dallas was one of them. A wily trapper, Dallas typified the rugged individualism that forged this country. He went too far when he killed two game wardens in 1981.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The World Trade Center Bombing
programme.desc: Terrorist bombings are what happen in other countries. Not here in the United States. And yet, in 1993, it happened in New York City.

programme.title: The FBI Files: John Gotti: Convicted
programme.desc: John Gotti was ambitious, powerful and ruthless. He ruled with flash and conspicuous style, playing celebrity with the media and cat and mouse with the FBI. They called John Gotti the Teflon Don. Serious charges just wouldn't stick.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The True Story of Mississippi Burning
programme.desc: Philadelphia, Mississippi, 1964. A sleepy southern town steeped in tradition finds itself targeted for invasion.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Master Plan
programme.desc: Willow Springs, Illinois, seemed like any other quiet Midwestern community. But it was really one of the most corrupt places in the nation. This tiny village, nestled just outside of Chicago, was in the hip pocket of organized crime.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Firefight
programme.desc: In Miami, a gang of robbers targeted banks and armored cars. They carried assault weapons and weren't afraid to use them. They struck during the day, and sometimes twice a day. For awhile, they seemed unstoppable.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Killer Abroad
programme.desc: Beginning in 1990, Europe found itself in the clutches of a serial killer. He became an international outlaw, hopping from country to country to evade capture and to kill again.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Moving Target
programme.desc: When a sniper in Utah started targeting African-American men for death, authorities launched a massive investigation. With scant clues and no witnesses they found the odds stacked against them, and they had no idea where the killer would strike next.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Mission
programme.desc: When a family was murdered in Arkansas, it seemed like an isolated event. But soon the crime was revealed to be part of an ever-widening circle of violence that defined a new age of domestic terrorism.

programme.title: The FBI Files
programme.desc: In 1995, our nation's capital was also our nation's murder capital. Even the police weren't safe. While Washington, DC, law enforcement targeted criminals, the criminals targeted law enforcement, even gunning down officers on patrol.

programme.title: The FBI Files: .22 Caliber Killer
programme.desc: In Buffalo, New York, a sniper targeted African-American men. He held a city hostage, and threatened to ignite a racial powder keg. And it looked like others might be following his bloody example.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.desc: Jarrad Howse takes Chill to the hidden surfing destination of Tofino in Canada. Cold, wet and windy but better yet, sublime surf! We catch up with the Pro's at the Cold Water Classic.

programme.title: Real Renovations: Comedy of Errors

programme.title: Real Renovations: 12 Days Left

programme.title: Real Renovations: Design Problems

programme.title: Real Renovations: All’s Well that Ends Well

programme.title: Real Renovations: Making Decisions
programme.desc: At the two-story reno, Jim Caruk gets into extra costs as he tries to explain the design problems to the home owners. Foreman Neil expresses his feelings. And Jim is finally finished the little face-lift that turned into a major event.

programme.title: Real Renovations: Shower Stories
programme.desc: The roof is finally figured out at the two-story reno, but what about the switches, the pot lights, the stucco - so many decisions, so little time. And Jim’s designer Robin experiences the highs and headaches of renovating her own home.

programme.title: Real Renovations: See What Happens
programme.desc: Foreman Neil gets down to all the nitty-gritty details at the two-story reno, including moving a 2000 pound shed. Meanwhile, Jim Caruk gives the home owners a tour and tries to mention money. At Jim’s house the kitchen gets redesigned.

programme.title: Real Renovations: Behind the 8-Ball
programme.desc: Significant problems at the two-story reno are stressing Jim Caruk out as costs soar and money is lost. At Jim’s house, Nick the landscaper makes Jim an offer he can’t refuse. And Jim starts a new job.

programme.title: Real Renovations: The Designated Designer
programme.desc: Jim Caruk breathes a sigh of relief as his problem-plagued two-story reno is finally finished. Elsewhere, a grungy garage comes down and a cute cottage goes up.

programme.title: Real Renovations: A Moving Story
programme.desc: Jim Caruk is happy to finally see the bricks go up at the painfully slow reno of his own home. Across town, we see a remarkably smooth little kitchen reno from start to finish.

programme.title: Real Renovations: Jim’s Happy Ending
programme.desc: In a rare moment, Jim Caruk straps on his tool belt and gets down to work at his house. Uptown, Jim builds a home theatre. While the results are remarkable, it was a rough ride for him. And finally, Jim takes a fond look back at this year’s jobs.

programme.title: Real Renovations: The Weather’s Killing Us
programme.desc: The Glengrove kitchen and family room renovation that started last year continues to drag on as delays, indecision and bad weather frustrate the homeowners. Jim also has to deal with a faulty floor he installed last year at his designer’s house.

programme.title: Real Renovations: Jim’s New House

programme.title: Green Paradise: Mexico: A Desert Between Two Seas

programme.title: Green Paradise: Chile: Desert Voices

programme.title: Green Paradise: Madagascar: A Multifaceted Land
programme.desc: Today, Madagascar has opened up and is finally showing itself to visitors, revealing the extent of its incredible natural and human resources.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Egypt: Water and Sand
programme.desc: Siwa is an island in the middle of the desert where the Great Sand Sea comes to rest at the foot of the date palms. This large oasis, bordered by two lakes of turquoise blue, is unique in Egypt and attracts travelers in search of authenticity.

programme.title: Green Paradise: South Africa: A Rainbow Nation
programme.desc: With its wide open spaces and pristine coastline, the province of KwaZulu-Natal has become one of the South Africa's eco-tourism havens. Away from the carefree atmosphere of its beaches, visitors witness the well-preserved flora and fauna.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Sri Lanka: The Emerald Isle
programme.desc: Today, Sri Lanka is known principally for the beauty and great diversity of its landscapes: heavenly beaches, mountains, falls, famous tea plantations and forests. This country has begun to preserve its ecological resources for future travelers.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Laos: Along the Mekong
programme.desc: Cut off from the rest of the world for 30 years, Laos is slowly opening up to tourism, but its environment and cultures are fragile. From the fishing villages to the forests in northern Laos, meet people who develop designs of environmental protection.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Australia: From the Ocean to the Vine
programme.desc: Surrounded on three sides by ocean, Margaret River in Western Australia is a small peninsula nestled in a corner of paradise! Its thousands of miles of coastlines and beaches contain magical, deserted, primeval places. Go surfind and pick wine grapes.

programme.title: Green Paradise: French Polynesia: Blue Lagoon
programme.desc: In the middle of the Pacific Ocean, the Tuamotus is one of the larges archipelagos in French Polynesia. Displaying stunning beauty, the islands now face the challenge of preserving the ecosystem of their coral gardens.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Dominican Republic - Caribbean Treasure
programme.desc: Explore the lesser known jungles, mountains, and lakes of the Dominican Republic.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Chile - In a Gentle and Savage Land
programme.desc: Discover Chilean Patagonia, an exceptional landscape of mountains, glaciers, rivers, and forests.

programme.title: Green Paradise: Morocco - The Magic of the Great South
programme.desc: Take a voyage to the rhythm and the undulations of the dunes of the Moroccan desert.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Antenas Loudspeakers and High Definition
programme.desc: This episode is dedicated to 'Animal Copyright' in communications. We 'see' communication, which cannot be seen but can be heard, smelled, felt or perceived, as a loud and clear message.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Lights, Signals, and Mirrors
programme.desc: Communication deserves special treatment. In this first episode dedicated to communication, we centre on visual language. Animal species that transmit information whilst maintaining eye contact.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Line, Web, Mesh, and Knot
programme.desc: We see by observing many animals that man is not the inventor but the discoverer of different artifacts or techniques.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Poisonous Drugs and Antidotes
programme.desc: Is it possible that animals have pharmaceutical knowledge of the power of certain substances? Why do species of curassow consume kaolin (china clay) after eating certain fruits?

programme.title: Natural Genius: Lotions, Creams, Combs and Unguents
programme.desc: Hygiene is synonymous of health, and the elaboration of techniques, above all for evolution of cleaning instruments, and this also implies a very elaborate and complex developmental behaviour.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Stilts, Soles, Wheels and Wings
programme.desc: Of the inventions that emerge from the nineteenth century industrial revolution, those that have permitted travel of people and objects are the inventions that have most influenced the human capacity to dominate and conquer the corners of the world.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Vessels, Flippers and Bathing Trunks
programme.desc: The evolutionary successes in which life has solved aquatic locomotion doubtlessly deserve a leading role in the episode "Animal Copyright". In fact, it is the second part of the theme dedicated to traveling methods.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Alarm, Nursery Schools and Security Systems
programme.desc: Tools destined for hunting and warfare are equally as important as those destined to protect, be it self-protection, or protection of descendants.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Hammers, Pickaxes, Shovels and Mattocks
programme.desc: Animals are extraordinary and surprising builders and their works vary greatly. In order to carry them out, they have either designed or made the most of a great amount of tools, utensils and building material.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Spears, Needes, Daggers and Barbs
programme.desc: Living creatures have designed an innumerable amount of sharp objects, be they for hunting or defense, or the battle of reproduction or territory.

programme.title: Natural Genius: Heaters, Fridges and Air Conditioners

programme.desc: The key ingredient to life in the universe is water. Until recently we thought Earth was the only place in the solar system to have any water at all. Now that probes are peering around nearby worlds we are finding that is just not the case.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Gravity
programme.desc: Gravity has long been a force that has intrigued scientists. Now, for the first time scientists are probing to detect gravity waves in space as well as mapping the gravity patterns of the moon.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Science and the Shuttle
programme.desc: For more than 25 years the shuttle was our ticket to space, and our laboratory in orbit. Uncover the legacy of this amazing machine, and see what lies ahead.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Landing on Mars
programme.desc: Mars sparks our curiosity like no other planet because it is so reachable. Despite having landed there, most of the information we gather is still done by instruments in the planet's orbit.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Milky Way
programme.desc: This episode traces our view of the Milky Way, from the mythology of ancient sky watchers to the efforts of scientists to map it from the inside out.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: The Big Bang
programme.desc: Throughout history, our nightly view of the universe has fueled our collective imagination. When it comes to the Big Bang, not even the most creative work of imagination can rival what science has revealed about the birth of the universe.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: The Hot Zone
programme.desc: Mercury is one Earth's closest neighbors, but for centuries it eluded astronomer's best efforts to learn its secrets. But that has changed thanks to missions like Mariner and most recently, Messenger.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Cosmic Rays
programme.desc: Cosmic rays can tell us much about the universe. They are not simply another form of light, but carriers of information about powerful and unseen processes at work thousands or even millions of light years away.

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Fermi Paradox
programme.desc: The Fermi Paradox asks the ultimate question: Given a few reasonable assumptions about the chance of life arising elsewhere in the universe and the distance between the stars, why has an alien civilization not presented itself?

programme.title: Cosmic Vistas: Landsat
programme.desc: Take a look at Landsat 8, the advanced planetary explorer with a 900 million dollar price tag! It is designed to peer across multiple wavelengths to reveal complex and ever-changing details that are undetectable by the human eye.

programme.title: How to Colonize the Stars
programme.desc: Leading physicists and engineers in the field of interstellar travel discuss some of the deep issues we face when considering the problem of sending spacecraft to other stars. Will mankind ever truly become a space fairing civilization?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Edge of the Universe
programme.desc: The night sky is a time machine. The further we look out into the universe, the further back in time we reach. Most of what we see is actually dark matter and dark energy, but its nature eludes us ... for the moment.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: The Astronauts
programme.desc: Who are these people that venture into space? Once they were test pilots, then scientists and engineers now teachers, politicians and paying tourists what does it take to earn the astronaut wings?

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Space: Getting There
programme.desc: The new surge in space transportation, privately owned companies vying for government contracts and private entrepreneurs looking to build hotels in space.

programme.title: Space: The New Frontier: Orbit

programme.desc: With low Earth orbit delegated to private companies, NASA is free to develop the deep space hardware for missions to Mars and beyond. The Orion space craft and SLS launch system are well on their way to delivering this capability.

programme.desc: A Canadian MTB adventurer explores Madagascar and shows the behind the scenes processes of making a film.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Girl Trouble
programme.desc: Dog and the team have girl trouble in this case. Krystal jumped bail and seems to have vanished into the high plains of Colorado. To make matters worse, she's running with her lover (and bond co-signer) Carrie. But Thelma and Louise they ain't.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Seeing the Light
programme.desc: Today Leland and Dog make a quick visit to the police supply store to get some new gadgets for the team but they can't linger because they've also got a fugitive to catch. Their target is reputed to have an explosive temper.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: When a Stranger Calls
programme.desc: When an offender with a long record ducks his day in court, Bobby Brown knows whom to call - The Dog!? And knowing that few souls can resist Beth's clever persuasion, Dog gives her the job of luring the fugitive in.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jack & Jill
programme.desc: Today's case is a twofer, a brother and sister both charged with drug related offenses. Also, Dog has crossed paths with the brother before. He once tried to stop Dog from arresting one of the most violent fugitives of his career.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Island Hopper
programme.desc: When a brother bondsman from Washington State calls Dog for help tracking a runner in search of fun in the sun on the tropical paradise of Kauai, the team gets on the case. Dog's only problem? No leads!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Nice Guys Finish Last
programme.desc: Dog and team help out a bondsman friend whose client jumped bail, but the target is a blank slate. Are his tattoos gang related? Is he likely to be violent? And making matters worse, when they hit his apartment they learn he is moving out.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Back Behind Bars
programme.desc: While tracking down a potentially dangerous ex-con facing a five year stretch in the big house, Leland struggles to find time to train and compete for his first boxing match in years.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Family Man
programme.desc: Dog and family head to Kona to track down a wanted father who's looking to bolt to the mainland to evade sentencing. Meanwhile, Dog does some evading of his own - Avoiding the much dreaded birthday party!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: All in the Family
programme.desc: Dog and the team need to help Leland hunt down some elusive fugitives. The case is a family affair with both mother and daughter in trouble with the law.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mother Courage
programme.desc: Dog knows that crime and drugs not only damage victims but also harm the families of the perpetrators, especially the kids. And both of the fugitives he's chasing today have left shattered families and struggling women in their wake.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bounty Boot Camp
programme.desc: Jim is a bondsman and longtime friend of Dog. Jim's son has just started in the family business. Today, Jim has asked Dog to track down a potentially dangerous fugitive, and take his son along for some training with the best in the world.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: True Identity
programme.desc: Dog knows that looks can be deceiving. The fugitive is pretty, petite, and trouble. She stands accused of settling an argument with the help of a box cutter. What Dog does not anticipate is how deceptive this femme fatale can truly be!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: What do you do when you have a fugitive you not only want to find, but believe can be helped back onto the straight and narrow? If you're Mary Ellen you call your good friend Dog.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Match Point
programme.desc: Duty calls and the Chapmans are off on a hunt. The team chases a fugitive who has disappeared into a world of "no known addresses.".

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Menehune Mischief
programme.desc: When Beth returns to the compound on the Big Island she finds a damaged SUV and two possible culprits - Dog or Justin. Pressed by Beth, Dog offers a third option. The perpetrators are Hawaii's mythical mischief makers - the Menehune!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mister Mom
programme.desc: It's been quite a while since Tim Chapman put down his mace can and bulletproof vest to care for his growing family. When his old friend Dog calls asking for help tracking an elusive felon, Tim jumps into action.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bait & Snitch
programme.desc: With the aid of the runner's girlfriend the posse heads out to bring a client with a checked past in. Little does the team suspect that before the end of the day Dog will be helping to mend a family torn apart by violence.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Scared Straight
programme.desc: Dog tracks a fugitive who is on the run from the law for the first time. Reading the file Dog knows the young man's life is at the crossroads. Will he be able to track down this wanna-be-gangsta in time to convince him to make the right choice?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: All My Children
programme.desc: For a guy who started life as a free spirited outlaw-biker Dog has certainly turned into a family man. His children touch everything he does today, from searching for the perfect gift for his daughter Cecily's birthday to hunting a fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Welcome to the Jungle
programme.desc: The hunt for an elusive and clever criminal takes Dog through the world of a bantam fighting cock, a pregnant daughter, and a jungle safe house go together. And don't forget the mopeds as well as a group of hostile squatters on government land!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bounty Baby
programme.desc: What's a father to do? When the cops ask Dog for help tracking down a renegade teen with a history of running hard, Baby Lyssa, eight months pregnant and counting, insists on joining the hunt. Can Dog keep his daughter safe and catch his man?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rain Check
programme.desc: For Dog and Beth it's not only another day in paradise, it's their anniversary. Beth is hoping for a romantic dinner with her man, but she knows only too well that for Dog work always comes first.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Love on the Run
programme.desc: Today Dog finds himself looking for more than one fugitive. He starts the day looking for a woman who has skipped out on her court date. But he soon learns that she has teamed up with a woman whose criminal exploits have attracted the local media.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Jump Start
programme.desc: Dog gave a break to a young man with a drug problem who promised to enter drug rehab. But this commitment to rehabilitation seems to have ended when he bolted from the car on the way to the drug treatment center and went on the run.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Ice Man
programme.desc: Dog's latest fugitive doesn't think small when it comes to illegal drugs: he was carrying almost a pound of meth when he was arrested. Now he's on the run with his pregnant girlfriend on the high plains of Colorado.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Trouble in Paradise
programme.desc: Dog is back in Hawaii and tracking a dangerous fugitive through the jungles of the Big Island. Their prey is being protected by a ring of family and friends that Dog must forcefully confront to bring in his man.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Girl Power
programme.desc: When Dog decides to spend the day caring for his newest granddaughter, Beth enlists the girls to hunt down a female fugitive. Heading into a dangerous part of town the ladies will use their feminine wiles to track this mother gone wrong.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Prodigal Son
programme.desc: Dog and his old friends, Tim Chapman and Sonny Westbrook are riding with the team, so their target, a thief with violent tendencies, is out of luck. When Dog learns that the fugitive is also a disrespectful son, he is more motivated to find his man.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Family Ties
programme.desc: Dog doesn't have the whole team today and he's got to catch a fugitive with a record of criminal assault. But when Dog finds the fugitive's former girlfriend, she thinks he isn't dangerous at all.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Special Delivery
programme.desc: For months, this fugitive has been stringing Leland along with a series of barely believable excuses. Out of patience, Leland calls in the Big Dog. The whole team heads out to put pressure on the family and friends of the fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surface Scratches
programme.desc: Dog's latest quarry is running from abuse and assault charges. As Dog investigates, he discovers that this fugitive has gamed the system by jumping from one bond, and one bondsman, to another.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Great Debate
programme.desc: When the co-signer of a bond is also romantically involved with the defendant, sometimes the bondman is put in the middle of a lover's quarrel.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Facebooked
programme.desc: Dog is in Denver helping Bobby Brown to track down a fugitive with a long rap sheet. But unfortunately they have no picture of the felon to work with, so the challenges are big on this one. But Dog discovers a new source; "Facebook".

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mano-a-Mano
programme.desc: Back in Colorado, Dog's on the hunt for a runner with more than a decade's worth of trouble with the law. But the fugitive's friends and family are reluctant to help Dog bring him in.
